    <string name="restricted_settings_title">Restricted setting on Android</string>
    <string name="restricted_settings_card_detail">If Espanso is greyed out or Android says this setting is unavailable, the APK was marked as sideloaded. Tap below, open the three-dot menu in App info, choose “Allow restricted settings,” then return to Accessibility and enable Espanso.</string>
    <string name="restricted_settings_message">Android blocks Accessibility for some apps installed from APK files. This security control cannot be bypassed by an app.\n\n1. Tap “Open App info.”\n2. Tap the three-dot menu at the top right.\n3. Choose “Allow restricted settings” and confirm.\n4. Return here and tap “Open Accessibility.”\n\nIf the menu is absent, reinstall through Google Play or another trusted app store/package installer supported by the device.</string>
